Another Oklahoma bill sanitized attempt to ban abortion

A few years ago, an Oklahoma bill was in existence which extended fetal homicide laws (as well as attempting to ban abortion in the state) to “save … infant or child,” according to Huffington Post.

As eye-rolling as language used by “pro-life” supporters might be, this blatant ban attempted to place the same legal status on women (or girls) who found themselves pregnant and attempted to terminate the pregnancy. This terrible bill “would have allowed unlawful termination of pregnancy charges even in the cases where a secretly pressured minor sought an abortion,” said Joni Marie Gutmanis of the local Southeast Oklahoma ACLU.
